<div class="kauer-logoblock" style="font-family:DEC Terminal Modern; font-size:17px"><big>Notice from the Kauer Research Organization:</big><br>
Due to the elusive nature of Entity 300 and the lack of information about Jennifer Hoffman, this document is in an incomplete state. Until completed, the page will serve as a collection of logs about those who've interacted with the entity. Testimonies in this page may contain inaccurate information, as accurate documentation of Entity 300 continues to be a challenge.</div>



<span style="color:white">---</span><span style="background:#145AF580; font-size:20px; font-family:VT323; padding:1px">File-001 : Survivor's Account of Entity 300 </span><br>
"I think I first noticed the entity when I was traveling in [[Level 324|<span style="color:black"><u>Level 324</u></span>]]. I was inside one of the gas stations just looking for supplies. When I got close to the exit, I noticed a collection of [[Entity 3|<span style="color:black"><u>Smilers</u></span>]] outside, I think. They noticed me as well, so they started coming inside, and I hid. For the time, I thought I was doing a good job avoiding them. Naturally you'd assume that, maybe it was the confidence getting to my head or something."

"Anyway, I got to the door, and the entities noticed me. Obviously I was going to race out of the building, yea? But once I stepped before the door, some bitch showed up in front of me. It looked human, with straight black hair and a bruised figure. If I wasn't so scared at that moment, I would've probably put some more bruises on them. The thing stared at me, slowly moving forward as it flickered in and out of my vision. (I) was moving faster than it, but I couldn't get the strength to just race by her. Something about her presence made me feel guilty. Like merely being around her made me a monster."

"But as quick as it came, it left, and I could feel the slimy breath of a Smiler going down my neck. I raced out of there after that and found an exit within a couple minutes. Something about that encounter though, it still plays through my head. It was just some normal oddity you'd find in the Backrooms, yea? But I can recall it so clearly though. For the few seconds we saw each other, it felt like there was a whole conversation happening between us. She sounded hurt, screaming at me that it was my fault."

"I don't know what was ''my fault'', she never told me. But I do feel guilty about it."



<span style="color:white">---</span><span style="background:#145AF580; font-size:20px; font-family:VT323; padding:1px">File-002 : Survivor's Account of Entity 300</span><br>
"I can't be fucked to figure out what part of [[Level 913|<span style="color:black"><u>Level 913</u></span>]] I was in when it happened. It's a lot of trains and I was climbing between them, that's what I'm sure of. At the moment, I think I had just got away from some Imitations, and I was pretty damn tired. My chest was rising and falling quick and whatever, and at the time I didn't have any [[Object 1|<span style="color:black"><u>Almond Water</u></span>]] on my person. So I was just sitting in one of the rail cars at the time. My friend at the time was across from me and he was looking to some of the other train cars, maybe to find a path through them? I don't know what he was thinking at the time, and I can't really ask him anymore, heh."

"What were we talking about at the time? I think it was something about escaping the level. We had been there for a few days at that point, and it was driving us insane, obviously. Not sure what level we were hoping to get to, but I'd end up in [[Level 11|<span style="color:black"><u>Level 11</u></span>]] after everything went down, which isn't that bad. Would've rather we found some place to noclip out rather than have to reach some documented exit though."

"Back to the incident, sorry. Before my friend was fucking crushed, we both hear whooshing from above us. Jokingly, we debated on who was gonna check, and I was volun-told to. Not a big deal. So I poked my head out of the train car and saw nothing. Instead, I immediately heard a large crashing noise coming from right nearby. I prolly' jumped like a foot into the air out of terror. And when I finally checked, my friend wasn't there. He was buried under metal framing from the train and nothing else. The mess of the situation made me numb at that moment. I didn't try to pull the rebar off him."

"Maybe I left him to die, but it was clear we had no chance either way to get him help. That's just how the Backrooms is yea? You don't know when the person next to you will just... disappear. I hope he clipped into another level, but I doubt it. There was a lot of red on those metal pieces."



<span style="color:white">---</span><span style="background:#145AF580; font-size:20px; font-family:VT323; padding:1px">File-003 : Survivor's Account of Entity 300 </span><br>
"It was a really nice day in fact, sun was out and I was just traveling across [[Level 300|<span style="color:black"><u>Level 300</u></span>]] at the time. I can't quite recall if I was with my friend Kelly at the time, since this was now a few weeks ago since I came across it. It doesn't matter too much though. When I first spotted Entity 300, it was when I was kneeling on the ground and looking over my supplies. What that supplies was, couldn't tell you. But I'd look up to see some sort of figure blotting out the sun. If I didn't move, I'd probably be dead."

"So I scrambled to the side and ''BANG'', there was a body on the ground like half a meter away from me. It looked to be some sort of woman, but her face was looking toward the ground and I didn't want to look further into it. It also smelled like shit. Like it was very fucking bad, Kelly might've gagged from the scent but I don't recall. The people in the Backrooms tend not to smell good, but this was far above that. It smelled like boiled pee mixed with a bunch of other rotten scents; spoiled milk, bad eggs, you know." 

"I got back onto my feet pretty quickly afterward too I can't confirm if we booked it right away, but we definitely started to run once another body fell to the ground. At that point we didn't turn to look either, just kept hearing ugly slamming noises as corpses rained down from above us. I remember asking whoever was with me if this was normal, and they didn't give a response."

"Once we got into [[Level 173|<span style="color:black"><u>Level 173</u></span>]], the falling bodies stopped. The silence was weirdly uncomfortable. I turned around then to see if I could see whatever was following us, but there was nothing there. Just me, Kelly, and the quiet beating of the river. It wouldn't leave my mind for a while. I think I was wondering about what I would've saw if I turned around. Would it have been the same person, disappearing and reappearing in the sky, just to try and crush us again? Unsure, but I doubt it would have have been fun to look at."



<span style="color:white">---</span><span style="background:#145AF580; font-size:20px; font-family:VT323; padding:1px">File-004 : Survivor's Account of Entity 300 </span><br>
"I think I was too busy looking over the washing machines and being self conscious to notice when the girl showed up. It was a laundromat after all, I was gonna try and clean some of my clothes. Ya' can't really find a shower around in the Backrooms unless you're at some sort of base. Which yea there is one in [[Level 291|<span style="color:black"><u>Level 291</u></span>]], but I didn't find it at the time. So I'm standing there, staring at the washing machine I was using and hoping it didn't become some sort of monster that'd eat all my clothes."

"At the time I was near a door too, a door to another chamber of laundry machines but a door. So I turn to look at it, and see someone standing there. Her head was jerking around like crazy and her clothes looked torn up. It seemed like some people attacked her. And damn she smelled, I should have realized by that point that I was staring at a corpse but... I don't know, I was too busy thinking about my own clothing. I think I asked her if she needed some money for the machines. Just some casual conversation to defuse the tension. She didn't seem to take kindly to the question though, as her body started slowly moving closer."

"Then I heard her talk, her mouth didn't move, but the voice was definitely coming from her."

''Er hat mich ausgetrickst!''

"It was like a fucking banshee. But as soon as she said it, she disappeared. I don't know what she said, or what I did, to deserve being yelled at by a ghost. I found a base later and shared the story there. That's how I got here, heh."

